o the skills of other disciplines, while sociologists and historians are encouraged to consider the value of film evidence in their own fields. This work should appeal to all readers interested in social history and in how cinema and society works.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picturesxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszGreat Britain. 0aWorking class in motion pictures. 0aWorking classzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aBritish cinema.  aBritish working-class community.  aauthority structure.  abuilt environment.  acareer criminals.  adance hall.  aindustrial disputes.  ainternalised values.  apostwar British films.  aworking-class people.1 aGillett, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614180440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141804423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141804/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles